  "market_context": "Tuesday Aug 6, 2024 on NQ 5-minute chart with hourly model overlay. Prior bearish structure with candle 3 closure. 9:30 open made a move higher, then traded lower into a swing low around 19,200. The 4-hour 6 AM candle formed a shallow wick supporting expansion higher into the 10 AM candle.",
  "key_observation": "A 6 AM 4-hour reversal candle with shallow wick aligns with a 10 AM continuation candle, offering multiple stacked entries: the V-shaped reversal off the 9:30 low (SMT + CISD), the 10 AM expansion continuation into a POI, and continuation entries after each new protected swing.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified prior bearish structure with a candle 3 closure on the higher timeframe context.",
    "Observed 9:30 open made a move higher, then sold off into a low forming a V-shaped reversal.",
    "Reasoned that if price reverses here, it should target the failure swing highs above as draw on liquidity.",
    "Checked the 4-hour: noted a fairly shallow wick on the prior 6 AM candle, supporting expansion higher, likely waiting for 10 AM.",
    "Confirmed SMT divergence and CISD on the lower timeframe, marking the first possible entry on the reversal with stop on the body low.",
    "Identified second entry: 10 AM continuation candle opens with shallow wicks on both 4H and 1H, expanding into a POI — fractally price not expected to revisit the low.",
    "Noted third entry: after consolidation and sweep forming a new protected swing, take continuation entry as long as 2R is available toward the high.",
    "Discussed not fading the expansion candle back into range; wait for the 2 PM candle close, then look for a reversal candle.",
    "Watched the 2 PM 4-hour candle sweep the prior high then deliver a CISD lower — a manipulation-and-distribution within the same 4H candle.",
    "Entered at open for that reversal (aggressive move limits retracement), targeting 2R; candle 4 continuation confirmed the move."
  ],
  "outcome": "Multiple targets hit: the initial long reversal trade closed at +$205.75 (R/R 2.94). Subsequent continuation entry into the high also reached target. The 2 PM reversal entry produced a candle 4 continuation lower as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "Align lower-timeframe entries with 4H candles whose wick signature supports expansion. A 6 AM reversal candle pairs with a 10 AM continuation candle; within a single 4H candle you can also get manipulation and distribution. Multiple valid entries exist — reversal, expansion, and continuation after protected swings — provided 2R is achievable.",
